Key Match Events: Jrue Holiday scored 12 points in the first quarter on 5-of-6 shooting.
Boston Celtics won 109-86 against Houston Rockets.
Holiday's performance helped limit Houston to just nine assists, the fewest by any NBA team in nearly three years.
Kristaps Porzingis returned to the lineup and contributed 11 points, five rebounds, two assists, and two blocks.
Post-Match Reflections: Mazzulla praised Holiday's aggressiveness and effort on both ends of the floor.
Mazzulla highlighted Porzingis' defensive impact in the second half.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Boston Celtics held Houston Rockets to 36.4 percent shooting from the floor and 27.8 percent from deep.
Houston was the second Celtics opponent in the last three games to be limited to 86 points or fewer.
